onscience in counterinsurgency. These wide-ranging essays shed new light on the fraught world of Pax Americana and on the ethical and political dilemmas faced by anthropologists and military personnel alike when attempting to understand and intervene in our world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCounterinsurgencyxUnited States. 0aCounterinsurgencyzUnited States. 0aPolitical anthropologyxUnited States. 0aPolitical anthropologyzUnited States. 0aWar and societyxUnited States. 0aWar and societyzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aBeckett, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBennett, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBishara, Amahl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaffrey, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastaño, Paola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Rochelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFosher, Kerry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarland, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález, Roberto J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffin, Marcus B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGusterson, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHevia, James L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobsen, Kurt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJauregui, Beatrice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJauregui, Beatrice, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKe